Privacy Policy
Cowboys & Indians
' Privacy Policy
Cowboys & Indians
is committed to taking reasonable measures to protect the privacy of our users. Please read the following for more information about our privacy policy regarding your use of our web site, the types of information we collect and what we do with it. This policy may change from time to time so please check back and review it periodically.
The Information We Collect and How We Use It
We will ask you for personal information when you purchase a product directly on the
Cowboys & Indians
site in order that we may process and fulfill your order. We may also ask you for personal information at other times, such as when you use our message boards. We may also keep records of any correspondence you send to us.
We monitor the web page viewing patterns and site usage of our visitors. From time to time, we may use the information we collect about you to send you e-mails about changes to the
Cowboys & Indians
site, new services and upcoming site features or special offers we think you would enjoy. If you would rather not receive this information, or if your personal information changes (such as your mailing address) or you wish to have it removed from our records, we will attempt to provide a way to correct, update or remove the personal data you give us if you contact our Webmaster at
webmaster@cowboysindians.com
.
Cowboys & Indians
may share certain information you provide with the retailers and manufacturers whose products and services are displayed on the site. We may also share aggregate statistics about our users with reputable advertisers, business partners, sponsors and other third parties, such as the breakdown of audience by gender, age group, and number of visits to the web pages for different films, television shows, promotional activities, products and services, but these statistics will include no personal identifying information.
Use of IP Addresses
When you open a web page, the computer acting as the server for that web page automatically assigns your computer a number called an IP address. The web server can then automatically identify your computer by its IP address.
Cowboys & Indians
may collect your computer's IP address to audit and administer the use of our site, as well as to report aggregate use information to our advertisers, to the manufacturers and retailers whose products and services are featured on our site, and to other third parties. Generally, our IP addresses do not contain any personally identifying information, so that your session will be logged, but your personal identity will remain anonymous in such logs (except if needed to identify a user when necessary to enforce compliance with our rules or terms of service or to protect our service, site, customers or others).
Use of Cookies
Through the web browser you use, a web site can transfer pieces of information called cookies about your use of the site to your hard drive. We use cookies to offer and provide you with customizable and personalized services, and to store and sometimes track information about you. We also use cookies to determine which areas on the
Cowboys & Indians
site are popular and which are not, and many improvements to the
Cowboys & Indians
site are made based on the total number of visitors and pages viewed. The use of cookies is standard in the Internet industry and you can find cookies being used at most major web sites.
You can usually set a browser's preferences to disable cookies, if you choose to do so, or to notify you when you are receiving a cookie, so that you can decide whether to accept it. Sometimes you may receive cookies from our advertisers or the web sites of the retailers or manufacturers whose products are displayed on the
Cowboys & Indians
site. We do not control these cookies. The use of advertising cookies sent by third-party servers is standard in the Internet industry.
Links to Other Web Sites or Internet Forums
There are links from the
Cowboys & Indians
site that will take you to other web sites outside of our control. These include links to our advertisers, the manufacturers and retailers whose products and services are featured on our site, and other third parties. Information you provide on other web sites accessible from the
Cowboys & Indians
site will be subject to the privacy policies posted on such web sites (which may provide less protection than our privacy policy), and you are encouraged to review the privacy policies posted on such sites.
Whenever you give out personal information online to other users, such as through message boards or chat rooms, such information can be collected and used by people you do not know.
Cowboys & Indians
cannot guarantee the security of any information you disclose online and you do so at your own risk.
Children and Personal Use of the Site
Cowboys & Indians
encourages parents and guardians to spend time with their children online, and to become familiar with the web sites their children visit. The
Cowboys & Indians
site is designed solely for users who are over the age of 18.
Your Consent
By using the
Cowboys & Indians
site, you consent to this privacy policy and the collection and use of information as described in this policy. If you do not agree to this policy, please do not use the
Cowboys & Indians
site. Your continued use of the
Cowboys & Indians
site following any posting of changes to these terms will mean you consent to such changes.
Your Feedback
Cowboys & Indians
welcomes your questions and comments about our privacy policy. Please send e-mails to
mail@cowboysindians.com
.